1
00:00:26,128 --> 00:00:29,063
[Oars Splashing]

2
00:00:40,442 --> 00:00:42,467
[Panting]

3
00:01:23,118 --> 00:01:27,077
[Panting Continues]

4
00:02:32,087 --> 00:02:35,022
[Horn Blowing]

5
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:45,728
[Horn Continues]

6
00:02:58,046 --> 00:03:02,449
[Train Approaches]

7
00:03:13,962 --> 00:03:15,862
- [Stereo: Loud Rock]
- [Woman] Roarke!

8
00:03:15,931 --> 00:03:17,865
- [Screaming]
- Roarke!

9
00:03:17,933 --> 00:03:22,097
I'm tellin' you for the 157th time,
turn that music off!

10
00:03:22,171 --> 00:03:26,471
It's singeing my hair!
You got to find your sneakers, buddy.

11
00:03:26,542 --> 00:03:28,294
- [Screams]
- Your old ones!

12
00:03:28,294 --> 00:03:29,158
- [Screams]
- Your old ones!

13
00:03:29,228 --> 00:03:32,163
Hey! See if you can
find Dad's sneakers!

14
00:03:32,231 --> 00:03:34,563
Dad? Come on, Mom.

15
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:36,624
- [Stops]
- Why bother?

16
00:03:36,702 --> 00:03:38,795
He's just gonna cancel.

17
00:03:38,871 --> 00:03:44,468
- Dad always cancels.
- Somethin' came up those other times.

18
00:03:44,543 --> 00:03:46,670
I have a stomachache
in my mouth.

19
00:03:46,745 --> 00:03:48,679
- Oh, God.
- You do?

20
00:03:48,747 --> 00:03:52,683
Here we go. She pretends she's sick
so we don't leave her.

21
00:03:52,751 --> 00:03:55,185
Oh, stop.
It's just for a few days.

22
00:03:55,254 --> 00:03:58,314
With those notorious psychos,
your grandparents!

23
00:03:58,390 --> 00:04:00,654
[Children Shouting, Door Opens]

24
00:04:00,726 --> 00:04:03,194
[Laughing]
Oh. Whoop, whoop, whoop.

25
00:04:03,262 --> 00:04:08,097
I almost got you packed.
Hi. I just can't find...

26
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:10,727
your old sneakers.

27
00:04:10,803 --> 00:04:14,102
Um, can I talk to you
for a second?

28
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:21,302
Oh, you're not gonna do this,
not three years in a row.

29
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:24,543
Roarke, you take your sister
in the other room.

30
00:04:24,616 --> 00:04:27,210
- Come on, Willa.
- And shut the door.

31
00:04:27,286 --> 00:04:31,382
- Don't make this harder than it is.
- What are we to you, Tom?

32
00:04:31,457 --> 00:04:36,121
Are we just some gaggle of obligations
pulling on you, making you tired?

33
00:04:36,195 --> 00:04:40,222
Gail, Selvaggio didn't like my drawings.
They just weren't good enough.

34
00:04:40,299 --> 00:04:44,395
- They're giving the project to Parker.
- So let Parker do it.

35
00:04:44,470 --> 00:04:47,803
Fine, so let Parker do it.
Maggie, get off the quilt.

36
00:04:47,873 --> 00:04:50,068
Maggie!

37
00:04:50,142 --> 00:04:52,906
Get off the quilt!

38
00:04:52,978 --> 00:04:55,310
Maggie, get down.

39
00:04:55,381 --> 00:04:57,315
Good girl.

40
00:04:57,383 --> 00:05:00,250
Gail, how did this
become such a big deal?

41
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:04,756
Oh, it's not as big as
the Selvaggio deal, clearly.

42
00:05:04,823 --> 00:05:07,314
But it is your son's
birthday again...

43
00:05:07,393 --> 00:05:09,725
and he thinks you don't
want to spend time with him.

44
00:05:09,795 --> 00:05:11,990
You understand that part?

45
00:05:19,805 --> 00:05:22,740
I do not treat you
like a baby.

46
00:05:22,808 --> 00:05:27,108
I treat you like a slob.
There's a difference. Oh!

47
00:05:27,179 --> 00:05:29,044
[Laughing]

48
00:05:29,114 --> 00:05:31,173
- Hi, Mom.
- Ohh.

49
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,981
Oh, look at you.
It's so good to see you.

50
00:05:35,054 --> 00:05:38,217
- Hey!
- It's good to see you too, Grandpa.

51
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:40,349
You have to sign, buddy.

52
00:05:40,426 --> 00:05:44,089
Hey! Oh, boy.
Oh, yeah.

53
00:05:44,163 --> 00:05:47,758
- You look good.
- Where's Tom?

54
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,767
- Well...
- He didn't want to come.

55
00:05:49,835 --> 00:05:53,532
No, no. He's working.
He's really busy right now.

56
00:05:53,605 --> 00:05:55,903
- Mags!
- [Barking]

57
00:05:55,974 --> 00:05:57,908
Maggie!

58
00:06:05,517 --> 00:06:09,283
[Sighs]
I think my marriage is over, Mama.

59
00:06:09,354 --> 00:06:11,288
Oh, Bean.

60
00:06:11,356 --> 00:06:13,688
Damn.

61
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:15,693
Well, he, uh...

62
00:06:15,761 --> 00:06:19,697
just can't seem to make
time for us anymore.

63
00:06:19,765 --> 00:06:23,633
He's let himself get
so beaten up by his job.

64
00:06:23,702 --> 00:06:27,661
He hates it, but he spends
every waking minute over there.

65
00:06:27,739 --> 00:06:31,072
He hasn't been home
one weekend since Christmas.

66
00:06:31,143 --> 00:06:35,512
I don't know what it is
that he's trying to prove...

67
00:06:35,581 --> 00:06:38,607
but I'm really sick
of the whole thing.

68
00:06:38,684 --> 00:06:40,618
I'm sick of the whole fight.

69
00:06:40,686 --> 00:06:43,883
Everything has become
unbelievably hard.

70
00:06:43,956 --> 00:06:48,416
Huh. Honey, forgive me,
but you don't know what hard is.

71
00:06:48,494 --> 00:06:51,622
That's because
you give yourself an out.

72
00:06:53,065 --> 00:06:54,999
In our generation,
we had no out.

73
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,194
That was the pact
of marriage.

74
00:06:57,269 --> 00:07:00,568
Do you think
if I gave myself an out...

75
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:05,667
with your father, given his
orneriness and his deafness...

76
00:07:05,744 --> 00:07:08,804
that I wouldn't
have taken it years ago?

77
00:07:14,153 --> 00:07:16,087
Mom.

78
00:07:27,099 --> 00:07:29,624
Here, let me take that one.

79
00:07:29,701 --> 00:07:31,635
- Roarke.
- Yeah.

80
00:07:31,703 --> 00:07:36,367
- Go buy me a map and get the tags.
- Okay.

81
00:07:36,441 --> 00:07:40,969
The ranger said I had to get tags.
I thought this was all I needed.

82
00:07:41,046 --> 00:07:44,573
This just confirms
your reservation.

83
00:07:44,650 --> 00:07:47,881
There you go.
Here's your three tags.

84
00:07:47,953 --> 00:07:49,887
If a ranger asks,
show them to him.

85
00:07:49,955 --> 00:07:54,449
- Can I buy those two first-aid kits?
- Sure. Make it 50 bucks even.

86
00:07:54,526 --> 00:07:56,687
Some of the Band-Aids are missing.

87
00:07:56,762 --> 00:08:00,664
- Guy tore his ear up on a fishhook.
- Ouch.

88
00:08:00,732 --> 00:08:03,565
Thank you very much.

89
00:08:07,005 --> 00:08:09,439
Here.
And could I have a map?

90
00:08:15,781 --> 00:08:18,511
I wish you were too, Pop.

91
00:08:18,584 --> 00:08:23,647
Remember the trip down
the Snake River when I was twelve?

92
00:08:25,324 --> 00:08:27,349
That was the greatest.

93
00:08:29,828 --> 00:08:32,296
Thanks.

94
00:08:32,364 --> 00:08:34,491
[Grunting]

95
00:08:34,566 --> 00:08:37,501
Whoa, there, partner.
Are you okay?

96
00:08:37,569 --> 00:08:39,503
Yeah, I just got
to get new feet.

97
00:08:39,571 --> 00:08:42,039
Until you do,
you better slow on down.

98
00:08:42,107 --> 00:08:45,338
- You went to that concert?
- What?

99
00:08:45,410 --> 00:08:48,208
Oh, yeah. Yeah.

100
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,714
- Great show.
- So you saw Jane's Addiction.

101
00:08:50,782 --> 00:08:53,114
Wish I could've seen them
before they broke up.

102
00:08:53,185 --> 00:08:57,053
- Uh-huh.
- So, you goin' down the river alone?

103
00:08:57,122 --> 00:08:59,386
No. Me and a couple
of my buddies.

104
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:02,222
- Who are you goin' with?
- My mom.

105
00:09:02,294 --> 00:09:04,819
Oh, yeah?
This is a pretty tough river.

106
00:09:04,896 --> 00:09:06,830
She used to be a guide here.

107
00:09:06,898 --> 00:09:09,696
She wants me to go down the river
before it gets polluted.

108
00:09:09,768 --> 00:09:11,395
What about your daddy?

109
00:09:11,470 --> 00:09:15,463
He had to stay home and
do one of his stupid drawings.

110
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:18,008
Too bad.

111
00:09:18,076 --> 00:09:21,307
- [Air Pumping]
- Is that your mom?

112
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:24,349
Yeah.

113
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:26,407
I'm Wade.
What's your name?

114
00:09:26,485 --> 00:09:28,419
- Roarke.
- Good to meet you, Roarke.

115
00:09:28,487 --> 00:09:30,887
Mom! Mom!
This is Wade.

116
00:09:30,956 --> 00:09:34,255
- He's goin' down the river too.
- Hi, Wade. I'm Gail.

117
00:09:34,326 --> 00:09:36,760
Great idea, showing Roarke the river
before they ruin it.

118
00:09:36,828 --> 00:09:38,955
[Chuckles]

119
00:09:39,031 --> 00:09:41,022
Wade!

120
00:09:41,099 --> 00:09:45,160
- Come on! We gotta go!
- Be right there.

121
00:09:45,237 --> 00:09:48,206
He tells me you used
to be a guide here.

122
00:09:48,273 --> 00:09:50,537
Oh! About 150 years ago.

123
00:09:50,609 --> 00:09:52,941
You must know the river
pretty well, then.

124
00:09:53,011 --> 00:09:55,946
- Well, I used to.
- How far you going?

125
00:09:56,014 --> 00:09:57,948
End of the line, Bridal Creek.

126
00:09:58,016 --> 00:09:59,950
Oh, yeah? Us too.

127
00:10:00,018 --> 00:10:03,181
- Oh, great.
- Come on, Wade! We're dyin' here!

128
00:10:03,255 --> 00:10:06,691
[Chuckles]
I wish I were going with you guys.

129
00:10:06,758 --> 00:10:08,817
[Laughing]

130
00:10:10,595 --> 00:10:12,722
Well.

131
00:10:12,798 --> 00:10:14,732
Here you go, Roarke.

132
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,791
Keep the sun
out of your eyes.

133
00:10:16,868 --> 00:10:20,065
Wow! No way!

134
00:10:20,138 --> 00:10:23,369
- What do you say, Roarke?
- Oh, yeah. Thanks.

135
00:10:23,442 --> 00:10:27,037
Well, uh, see you
on the river, I guess.

136
00:10:27,112 --> 00:10:29,239
I don't know.
We're gonna be goin' fast.

137
00:10:29,314 --> 00:10:32,180
- [Man] Let's go, Wade!
- I'm comin'. I'm comin'.

138
00:10:33,247 --> 00:10:35,681
[Man #1]
I said the right oar!

139
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:39,015
- [Man #2] Okay, the right one!
- Yeah! Take it!

140
00:10:39,086 --> 00:10:41,054
Get off my damn foot!

141
00:10:41,122 --> 00:10:43,682
[Gail] lt'll be a long haul
with him at the oars.

142
00:10:43,758 --> 00:10:46,124
Guy in back
knows what he's doing.

143
00:10:46,194 --> 00:10:48,754
Frank used to be
a guide on the Colorado.

144
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:51,355
- Push with both oars!
- [Roarke] It's Dad!

145
00:10:51,432 --> 00:10:53,866
[Willa]
Daddy!

146
00:10:53,935 --> 00:10:59,066
Is this where you sign up
for river rafting lessons?

147
00:11:00,775 --> 00:11:04,108
I got a dry jacket
and a pair of reef walkers.

148
00:11:04,178 --> 00:11:07,705
The guy at the camping store
said that's all I'll need.

149
00:11:07,782 --> 00:11:10,444
[Laughs]
What happened to Mr. Selvaggio?

150
00:11:10,518 --> 00:11:12,452
I brought him with me.

151
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:16,513
Let's go boys.
One... two... three.

152
00:11:16,591 --> 00:11:19,116
Let's do it!
Jump on!

153
00:11:19,193 --> 00:11:23,425
- [Willa] Bye-bye, Mommy!
- See you at Bridal Creek!

154
00:11:23,497 --> 00:11:25,829
Whoa!
[Chuckling]

155
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:28,425
Whoa! That's it!

156
00:11:28,502 --> 00:11:32,268
I love you too!

157
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,728
Roarke.

158
00:11:55,796 --> 00:11:58,094
Roarke.

159
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,792
Roarke!

160
00:12:10,244 --> 00:12:12,678
It's beautiful.

161
00:12:12,747 --> 00:12:15,079
- Yeah.
- Really.

162
00:12:16,884 --> 00:12:18,818
[Sighs]

163
00:12:31,465 --> 00:12:35,401
Okay, sweetie,
put your helmet on, please.

164
00:12:35,469 --> 00:12:37,300
Mom.

165
00:12:37,371 --> 00:12:41,102
You don't have to wear it all the time,
but we got some rapids comin' up here.

166
00:12:43,077 --> 00:12:46,706
- Just give me a hand, damn it!
- It's coming up!

167
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:50,850
You all right?

168
00:12:50,918 --> 00:12:53,944
[Gail]
If you're gonna sit there in the back...

169
00:12:54,021 --> 00:12:56,956
you should sit on
the floor in the center.

170
00:12:57,024 --> 00:13:00,187
- I can't see from there.
- Well, then, sit in front.

171
00:13:00,261 --> 00:13:02,229
I like it here.

172
00:13:02,296 --> 00:13:04,696
Okay.

173
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:08,701
[Roarke]
Here we go!

174
00:13:08,769 --> 00:13:10,896
Woo-hoo! Heh!
[Laughing]

175
00:13:10,972 --> 00:13:13,998
Wow, this is great!
[Shouting]

176
00:13:17,445 --> 00:13:20,414
[Roarke]
Yes! Hold on, Maggie!

177
00:13:22,683 --> 00:13:27,711
[Roarke Whooping]
Look out for that rock!

178
00:13:34,762 --> 00:13:36,696
Ohh!

179
00:13:36,764 --> 00:13:39,392
- [Laughing]
- Whoa!

180
00:13:40,634 --> 00:13:44,434
That was great!
But where's Dad?

181
00:13:44,505 --> 00:13:46,939
[Laughing]
He's swimming.

182
00:13:49,276 --> 00:13:52,541
- [Gail] Point your feet down!
- Point your toes, Dad!

183
00:13:52,613 --> 00:13:56,674
Could you just stop laughing
for a second and help me into the boat?

184
00:13:56,751 --> 00:13:58,981
- [Laughing Stops]
- [Moaning]

185
00:13:59,053 --> 00:14:00,953
- Ohh!
- Oh!

186
00:14:01,022 --> 00:14:03,217
[Moaning]

187
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:06,282
Is this the biggest one, Mom?

188
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,294
The biggest one's
the Gauntlet.

189
00:14:08,362 --> 00:14:10,296
That's a five-plus.

190
00:14:10,364 --> 00:14:12,798
That's off the scale.

191
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:16,598
- When do we do that one?
- Well, we don't do that one.

192
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:19,639
That's after the take-out
at Bridal Creek.

193
00:14:19,707 --> 00:14:22,904
- You can't go down there.
- Have you ever done it?

194
00:14:22,977 --> 00:14:26,435
- Mom is saying it's too dangerous.
- For you, maybe.

195
00:14:26,514 --> 00:14:29,449
Roarke. Honey,
I went down the Gauntlet...

196
00:14:29,517 --> 00:14:33,283
when I was 18 years old
with two other guides...

197
00:14:33,354 --> 00:14:35,288
experienced guides.

198
00:14:35,356 --> 00:14:37,950
And we were just lucky.

199
00:14:38,025 --> 00:14:41,961
But there were two other people
that summer who did not get so lucky.

200
00:14:42,029 --> 00:14:46,523
One guy got killed,
and the other one is paralyzed for life.

201
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:51,196
Don't worry. We're gonna hit
some threes and some four-pluses...

202
00:14:51,272 --> 00:14:55,174
and we will risk death
a number of times on this trip.

203
00:14:55,242 --> 00:14:58,575
So you're gonna scream,
you're gonna be so happy.

204
00:15:00,314 --> 00:15:03,977
- Hey, look, Mom, there's Wade!
- [Gail] Hello, the shore!

205
00:15:04,051 --> 00:15:07,214
- [Wade] Hello, the boat!
- Is everybody okay?

206
00:15:07,288 --> 00:15:10,451
- Yeah, I just got a cramp!
- We're trying to work it out.

207
00:15:10,524 --> 00:15:13,152
Hey, who's your friend, Gail?

208
00:15:13,227 --> 00:15:17,186
Oh, this is Tom,
uh, Roarke's father.

209
00:15:17,264 --> 00:15:21,132
Oh, no. You didn't tell him
about us, did you?

210
00:15:21,202 --> 00:15:23,227
[Laughing] No.

211
00:15:23,304 --> 00:15:27,741
Hey, Roarke!
Don't tell those fish we're comin'!

212
00:15:29,977 --> 00:15:33,913
[Gail] All right,
let's bring a little line in, okay?

213
00:15:33,981 --> 00:15:37,075
We're gonna aim for that ripple
right over there. See?

214
00:15:37,151 --> 00:15:39,210
Ten, two, ten, two...

215
00:15:39,286 --> 00:15:41,220
ten, release!

216
00:15:41,288 --> 00:15:42,915
Then let go of your line.

217
00:15:42,990 --> 00:15:46,926
Why don't you ask your dad
if he wants to come over?

218
00:15:46,994 --> 00:15:50,327
Hey, Dad, you wanna try this?

219
00:15:50,397 --> 00:15:52,524
Not now!
Thanks, buddy!

220
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:56,263
[Roarke] Do you think
he even knows he left Boston?

221
00:15:56,337 --> 00:15:58,771
Yeah, he knows.

222
00:15:58,839 --> 00:16:03,674
But he took two planes
and a charter just to get here, so...

223
00:16:03,744 --> 00:16:05,678
let's give him a break.

224
00:16:05,746 --> 00:16:09,842
- Try it again.
- Why are you suddenly on his side?

225
00:16:09,917 --> 00:16:12,852
I'm on everybody's side.
I'm the mother.

226
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:15,388
- [Gasps] You got it! That's it!
- Look, Mom!

227
00:16:15,456 --> 00:16:18,914
You got a nice one, buddy.
He's a beauty.

228
00:16:18,993 --> 00:16:20,927
Let's get him.
There he is.

229
00:16:20,995 --> 00:16:22,929
Come here.
Come here, sweetheart.

230
00:16:22,997 --> 00:16:26,899
Look, Daddy.
Oh, it's a monster.

231
00:16:26,967 --> 00:16:29,435
You know,
this is the first time...

232
00:16:29,503 --> 00:16:33,098
we've all had dinner together
since Mom's birthday.

233
00:16:36,777 --> 00:16:40,543
Hello, the Gail, Roarke
and Tom family!

234
00:16:40,614 --> 00:16:43,139
This is the Wade raft
passing you by!

235
00:16:43,217 --> 00:16:46,414
Hey, Wade!
I caught two fish today!

236
00:16:46,487 --> 00:16:48,682
First time I ever fished!

237
00:16:48,756 --> 00:16:50,781
Must be that lucky hat!

238
00:16:50,858 --> 00:16:56,694
Hey, Roarke, if that hat's so lucky,
I want it back!

239
00:17:12,379 --> 00:17:15,177
Hi.

240
00:17:15,249 --> 00:17:18,343
- He's down.
- Mm-hmm.

241
00:17:18,419 --> 00:17:21,445
- [Sighs]
- Well, had a big day.

242
00:17:25,526 --> 00:17:28,290
It's kind of warm.

243
00:17:30,331 --> 00:17:32,356
That's the way I like it.

244
00:17:39,273 --> 00:17:43,073
Did you finish
your sketches yet?

245
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:48,275
No. No, I didn't.

246
00:17:48,349 --> 00:17:50,647
And it's not a sketch, Gail.

247
00:17:50,718 --> 00:17:54,176
- You know, it's very important.
- Very important, I know.

248
00:17:54,255 --> 00:17:56,189
- So, tomorrow...
- What?

249
00:17:56,257 --> 00:18:00,057
Could you just pretend
to like it here a little bit?

250
00:18:00,127 --> 00:18:02,561
For Roarke's sake,
if not for mine.

251
00:18:02,630 --> 00:18:07,567
I don't do too bad at pretending
to like your stuff, so...

252
00:18:10,638 --> 00:18:14,233
Is that what you do?
Pretend to like my stuff?

253
00:18:14,308 --> 00:18:18,244
- No. You know, that's not what I mean.
- You don't have to.

254
00:18:18,312 --> 00:18:22,510
And just don't.
And don't do me any favors, either.

255
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:25,381
I don't.

256
00:18:27,354 --> 00:18:29,288
I won't.

257
00:18:34,028 --> 00:18:35,962
Gail.

258
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:40,057
- Listen, don't you ever realize...
- Let's just stop, okay?

259
00:18:40,134 --> 00:18:42,364
You never...
Oh, please!

260
00:18:45,005 --> 00:18:47,098
[Gail Laughing]

261
00:18:47,174 --> 00:18:49,734
[Screaming]

262
00:18:49,810 --> 00:18:53,473
- [Laughing]
- [Roarke] Whoa, it's cold!

263
00:18:53,547 --> 00:18:55,447
Whoo!

264
00:18:55,516 --> 00:18:57,541
[Maggie Barking]

265
00:19:01,989 --> 00:19:05,083
[Roarke Whooping]

266
00:19:05,159 --> 00:19:07,650
Wow!

267
00:19:08,729 --> 00:19:12,495
Hey, look, Mom!
Graffiti!

268
00:19:12,566 --> 00:19:14,796
Oh, wow!

269
00:19:14,868 --> 00:19:18,269
Those are pictographs.
They were made by people...

270
00:19:18,339 --> 00:19:21,467
who lived here thousands of years
before white men came.

271
00:19:21,542 --> 00:19:23,567
So those are their hands?

272
00:19:23,644 --> 00:19:26,374
Those markings might've been
made by a boy your age...

273
00:19:26,447 --> 00:19:28,938
while he was
on his vision quest.

274
00:19:29,016 --> 00:19:31,746
See?

275
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:36,356
Are you sure there's
fish around here, Mom?

276
00:19:37,624 --> 00:19:40,286
Over there, honey.

277
00:19:42,429 --> 00:19:44,363
Right in the current.

278
00:19:44,431 --> 00:19:46,922
- [Maggie Whimpers]
- Hey there!

279
00:19:49,636 --> 00:19:51,570
We've been waitin' for you.

280
00:19:51,638 --> 00:19:55,597
I should've suspected something
when he had us camp at the walk-out.

281
00:19:55,676 --> 00:19:58,611
Frank and Terry'd been
arguing most of the day.

282
00:19:58,679 --> 00:20:01,614
Frank used to be married
to my sister...

283
00:20:01,682 --> 00:20:03,616
until she realized
what a butthole he was.

284
00:20:03,684 --> 00:20:06,619
Anyway, Frank said things
he shouldn't have said.

285
00:20:06,687 --> 00:20:09,622
And this morning,
we woke up and he was gone.

286
00:20:09,690 --> 00:20:12,716
Why didn't you guys just follow him out,
walk out with him?

287
00:20:12,793 --> 00:20:15,694
That would have been
the smart thing to do...

288
00:20:15,763 --> 00:20:18,163
but I didn't want
to give him the satisfaction.

289
00:20:18,232 --> 00:20:21,201
And what he was doin' with the oars
didn't look that hard...

290
00:20:21,268 --> 00:20:25,534
so we just headed downriver...
and we saw this.

291
00:20:25,606 --> 00:20:28,541
That's when we decided
to wait for you guys.

292
00:20:28,609 --> 00:20:32,204
- Wade said you used to be a guide here.
- Yeah. Roarke, come over here.

293
00:20:32,279 --> 00:20:35,737
Is there any way
we could walk out of here...

294
00:20:35,816 --> 00:20:39,217
- like go up the canyon and...
- Uh, well, you might...

295
00:20:39,286 --> 00:20:42,744
but once you got up
to that canyon rim...

296
00:20:42,823 --> 00:20:46,452
and headed back to the ranger station,
there's a huge gorge.

297
00:20:46,527 --> 00:20:49,155
You'd have to walk around it.

298
00:20:49,229 --> 00:20:52,960
Even if you had the equipment
and knew what you were doing...

299
00:20:53,033 --> 00:20:56,730
and where you were going,
it'd take you five or six days.

300
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:02,673
Looks like we're stuck.

301
00:21:02,743 --> 00:21:04,677
Well, we...

302
00:21:04,745 --> 00:21:09,011
- I could get you as far as Bridal Creek.
- Yeah.

303
00:21:10,184 --> 00:21:13,881
We... wouldn't want
to be a burden.

304
00:21:14,988 --> 00:21:17,218
Well...

305
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:20,920
it doesn't look
like you have much choice.

306
00:21:20,994 --> 00:21:23,622
All right.

307
00:21:23,697 --> 00:21:26,689
[Gail]
Anyway, it's not as bad as it looks.

308
00:21:26,767 --> 00:21:29,895
- You just got to stay to the right.
- Maggie!

309
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:32,803
There's a bad hole on the left.
Don't hit that.

310
00:21:32,873 --> 00:21:33,897
No.

311
00:21:33,974 --> 00:21:36,465
[Roarke]
Come on, Mags! Time to go!

312
00:21:36,543 --> 00:21:40,479
Honey, would you go up
and get her?

313
00:21:40,547 --> 00:21:45,143
Stay to the right, and if you
do go swimming, which you won't...

314
00:21:45,219 --> 00:21:49,246
point your feet downstream
and hold on to your jacket.

315
00:21:49,323 --> 00:21:51,587
Just let
the current take you.

316
00:21:51,658 --> 00:21:54,092
Don't command the river.
Let the river command you.

317
00:21:54,161 --> 00:21:58,359
Hey, I don't live my life like that,
and I don't think you do, either.

318
00:21:58,432 --> 00:22:00,297
[Chuckling]

319
00:22:00,367 --> 00:22:02,301
Maggie!

320
00:22:02,369 --> 00:22:04,599
Maggie! Come!

321
00:22:04,671 --> 00:22:06,901
[Whistles]
Come on, girl!

322
00:22:06,974 --> 00:22:10,603
- [Maggie Barking]
- Maggie!

323
00:22:10,677 --> 00:22:12,702
- [Whimpering, Digging]
- Maggie, come.

324
00:22:14,515 --> 00:22:16,642
What do you got there, girl?

325
00:22:16,717 --> 00:22:21,086
- [Digging, Whimpering Continue]
- You all right, girl?

326
00:22:21,154 --> 00:22:23,748
[Roarke]
Maggie, come!

327
00:22:23,824 --> 00:22:26,850
- [Barking]
- Come, Maggie!

328
00:22:30,597 --> 00:22:33,088
[Barking]

329
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:35,691
Dogs.

330
00:22:35,769 --> 00:22:38,329
Yeah.

331
00:22:44,852 --> 00:22:49,221
- Buckle your life jacket. Stay right.
- [Wade] All right.

332
00:22:49,290 --> 00:22:51,224
- Just relax.
- Relax, huh?

333
00:22:51,292 --> 00:22:54,090
Yeah. Relax.

334
00:22:54,161 --> 00:22:58,063
- I want you to be the best you can be.
- Best I can be.

335
00:22:58,132 --> 00:23:02,432
Let me get down there first.
I'll be waitin' for ya.

336
00:23:02,503 --> 00:23:05,666
All right!
Come on, Maggie! Here we go!

337
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:07,674
Tom, better put the map away.

338
00:23:07,742 --> 00:23:10,677
We're gonna go through
our first whoop-dee-doos.

339
00:23:10,745 --> 00:23:14,272
- You might want to take a secure seat.
- What?

340
00:23:14,348 --> 00:23:17,545
- Here we go!
- Hold on, Roarke!

341
00:23:17,618 --> 00:23:21,418
[Roarke Shouting, Whooping]

342
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:25,618
[Roarke Laughing, Shouting]

343
00:23:25,693 --> 00:23:28,287
[Groaning]

344
00:23:28,362 --> 00:23:31,763
Here we go!
[Whooping]

345
00:23:31,832 --> 00:23:34,926
[Roarke Laughing, Shouting]

346
00:23:35,002 --> 00:23:37,163
[Shouting]

347
00:23:39,340 --> 00:23:41,831
[Shouting, Laughing Continue]

348
00:23:44,478 --> 00:23:46,878
- Oh, great!
- Oh, boy.

349
00:23:46,947 --> 00:23:49,074
[Roarke Shouting]

350
00:23:51,018 --> 00:23:52,952
All right.

351
00:23:53,020 --> 00:23:55,284
Here we go.

352
00:24:00,227 --> 00:24:03,788
She said stay on the right,
remember?

353
00:24:03,864 --> 00:24:06,230
- You remember, right?
- Oh, man.

354
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,530
[Wade]
She wasn't playing around.

355
00:24:10,104 --> 00:24:12,595
Whoo!

356
00:24:14,575 --> 00:24:16,509
Go right!

357
00:24:18,012 --> 00:24:21,778
Get us over, Wade!
Oh, shit!

358
00:24:21,849 --> 00:24:24,181
Oh, my God.

359
00:24:24,251 --> 00:24:28,119
- The right, Wade! To the right!
- Shut up!

360
00:24:30,791 --> 00:24:34,227
Oh, my God!
They're on the wrong side!

361
00:24:34,295 --> 00:24:37,162
Get over!
You gotta turn!

362
00:24:37,231 --> 00:24:41,429
[Terry Shouts]
There's a rock here!

363
00:24:41,502 --> 00:24:43,800
Wade!

364
00:24:46,941 --> 00:24:49,341
[Screaming]

365
00:24:59,119 --> 00:25:01,349
Get in the front!
We're gonna pick 'em up!

366
00:25:01,422 --> 00:25:03,447
[Gasping]

367
00:25:05,526 --> 00:25:07,551
Wade's lost his jacket!

368
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:16,864
Wade can't swim!
He's back there! He can't swim!

369
00:25:16,937 --> 00:25:19,804
Pull him in!
Pull him in!

370
00:25:19,874 --> 00:25:22,468
Get in the back.
We're goin' to him!

371
00:25:22,543 --> 00:25:24,875
[Tom]
There he is!

372
00:25:27,448 --> 00:25:30,542
[Terry]
Wade! Hold on, buddy!

373
00:25:30,618 --> 00:25:32,609
[Roarke]
Wade!

374
00:25:32,686 --> 00:25:34,620
[Tom]
He went under!

375
00:25:34,688 --> 00:25:36,451
Wade!

376
00:25:36,524 --> 00:25:39,584
[Roarke]
Where is he?

377
00:25:39,660 --> 00:25:42,060
He's still under!

378
00:25:42,129 --> 00:25:44,620
- Get the throw bag, Roarke!
- Hold on, Wade!

379
00:26:01,749 --> 00:26:04,741
[Terry]
Right there!

380
00:26:23,871 --> 00:26:26,339
- [Gasping]
- [Gail] Here's the rope! Over here!

381
00:26:26,407 --> 00:26:29,433
- [Terry] You okay?
- Wow, Dad!

382
00:26:29,510 --> 00:26:32,911
[Terry]
Come on, man. We got ya.

383
00:26:32,980 --> 00:26:35,107
- Tom!
- Hey, Wade!

384
00:26:35,182 --> 00:26:38,640
You almost drown!

385
00:26:38,719 --> 00:26:42,712
Wow! One of these days
I have got to learn how to swim.

386
00:26:45,693 --> 00:26:48,025
You okay? Nice job.

387
00:26:48,095 --> 00:26:50,962
I'm okay.

388
00:26:56,003 --> 00:26:59,029
Oh, I got that.
I got it.

389
00:26:59,106 --> 00:27:02,337
Okay.

390
00:27:06,146 --> 00:27:09,582
I want to thank you, Tom.
You saved my life.

391
00:27:09,650 --> 00:27:11,914
Oh, don't worry about it.

392
00:27:11,986 --> 00:27:14,648
You didn't have
to hit me, though.

393
00:27:17,558 --> 00:27:19,492
Yes, I did.

394
00:27:27,334 --> 00:27:30,497
[Indistinct, On Radio]

395
00:27:30,571 --> 00:27:33,904
[Gail] Just turn it around.
Get it straight up and down.

396
00:27:33,974 --> 00:27:35,908
- Pull out some.
- All right.

397
00:27:35,976 --> 00:27:39,776
[Gail] Point that thumb
where you want the fly to go.

398
00:27:39,847 --> 00:27:42,042
- Ten and two and release.
- [Continues On Radio]

399
00:27:42,116 --> 00:27:44,050
[Man On Radio]
At the top of the news:

400
00:27:44,118 --> 00:27:46,951
The car believed to have been used in
the robbery of the livestock auction...

401
00:27:47,021 --> 00:27:49,888
at the Flathead County Fairgrounds
Sunday was found abandoned...

402
00:27:49,957 --> 00:27:52,289
on a back road
near the Canadian border...

403
00:27:52,359 --> 00:27:55,795
in the robbery that netted
nearly a quarter of a million dollars.

404
00:27:55,863 --> 00:27:59,799
- A security guard was killed.
- What? What'd I do?

405
00:27:59,867 --> 00:28:03,428
My dad's been telling
my mother for 30 years...

406
00:28:03,504 --> 00:28:06,837
that they're going to rob
this cattle auction.

407
00:28:06,907 --> 00:28:09,398
- And finally somebody did it.
- Cattle auction?

408
00:28:09,476 --> 00:28:12,570
He's gonna be very happy.
Yeah, on the radio.

409
00:28:12,646 --> 00:28:14,580
- They just...
- Wow.

410
00:28:14,648 --> 00:28:18,277
You guys known each other
a long time?

411
00:28:18,352 --> 00:28:21,150
Me and Wade go way back.

412
00:28:21,221 --> 00:28:23,485
We just met Frank in Tulsa.

413
00:28:23,557 --> 00:28:26,958
L... I thought Frank
was married to your sister.

414
00:28:27,027 --> 00:28:31,657
- Oh, yeah. She lives in Tulsa.
- Oh.

415
00:28:31,732 --> 00:28:35,224
So what do you do when you're not
trying to drown yourself on a river?

416
00:28:35,302 --> 00:28:38,465
- I'm a skier, ski bum.
- Oh, yeah?

417
00:28:40,007 --> 00:28:42,100
What about you?
What do you do?

418
00:28:42,176 --> 00:28:46,545
I teach history
for a school for the deaf.

419
00:28:46,613 --> 00:28:49,844
Tom is an architect.

420
00:28:49,917 --> 00:28:52,886
I could tell you were a teacher.

421
00:28:52,953 --> 00:28:54,944
- Little bossy?
- No, no.

422
00:28:55,022 --> 00:28:58,321
- Ladies sure do like Wade.
- Yeah?

423
00:28:58,392 --> 00:29:00,292
[Gail]
Let's try again.

424
00:29:00,360 --> 00:29:03,921
- Ten, two, ten, two.
- Yeah, sure do.

425
00:29:03,997 --> 00:29:06,158
You keep trying to bring
your left hand up.

426
00:29:09,937 --> 00:29:11,871
Hey, Tom.

427
00:29:15,642 --> 00:29:19,237
[Acid Rock Emanating
From Headphones]

428
00:29:21,281 --> 00:29:23,749
I don't like those guys.

429
00:29:23,817 --> 00:29:26,183
I think we should leave
them behind tomorrow.

430
00:29:26,253 --> 00:29:29,484
They're all right.
They're just those kind of guys...

431
00:29:29,556 --> 00:29:32,684
that just never
got over their adolescence.

432
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,694
There's lots of them up here.

433
00:29:34,762 --> 00:29:37,663
Why are you defending him?

434
00:29:39,066 --> 00:29:43,400
Who? Wade?

435
00:29:43,470 --> 00:29:46,064
- I'm not defending him.
- Yes, you are.

436
00:29:46,140 --> 00:29:49,769
You sound like you're jealous.

437
00:29:49,843 --> 00:29:52,334
I'm not jealous...

438
00:29:52,412 --> 00:29:55,074
even though you did
drape yourself all over him.

439
00:29:55,149 --> 00:29:58,744
I did not drape myself.

440
00:29:58,819 --> 00:30:02,152
That is the way you teach
somebody to fly cast, honey.

441
00:30:02,222 --> 00:30:04,656
Oh, Gail. He knew exactly
what he was doing.

442
00:30:04,725 --> 00:30:09,628
Well, you know, they did get in over
their heads and they lost their guide.

443
00:30:09,696 --> 00:30:13,257
If something happened to me, and you
and Roarke were alone on the river...

444
00:30:13,333 --> 00:30:15,324
I would want somebody
to help you.

445
00:30:15,402 --> 00:30:17,768
I'm sorry.
Maybe I am being a jerk about Wade.

446
00:30:17,838 --> 00:30:22,571
But that still doesn't change
that I just think... something's off.

447
00:30:24,344 --> 00:30:26,312
- [Barking]
- Go get it, Maggie.

448
00:30:28,916 --> 00:30:30,941
Bring it here. Come on.

449
00:30:31,018 --> 00:30:35,682
- [Humming]
- [Roarke] Good girl, good girl.

450
00:30:35,756 --> 00:30:39,055
- [Maggie Barking]
- [Roarke] Go get it, Maggie.

451
00:30:41,195 --> 00:30:45,393
- Hey, Gail.
- Hey.

452
00:30:45,465 --> 00:30:50,129
- I found a hot spring.
- Yeah, isn't it great?

453
00:30:50,204 --> 00:30:54,402
If you feel the water down here,
it's really warm.

454
00:30:54,474 --> 00:30:58,501
- Oh, man. People.
- [Roarke] Go get it, Maggie.

455
00:30:58,579 --> 00:31:01,673
- Yeah.
- Good, good girl.

456
00:31:01,748 --> 00:31:05,047
Listen, I was wonderin', uh...

457
00:31:05,118 --> 00:31:07,586
What's the river like
below Bridle Creek?

458
00:31:07,654 --> 00:31:11,556
Oh, it's really spectacular down there.
It's unbelievable.

459
00:31:11,625 --> 00:31:13,752
Then how come people
don't go down there?

460
00:31:13,827 --> 00:31:16,591
Well, you're not allowed
to take rafts down there anymore.

461
00:31:16,663 --> 00:31:20,497
It's just... Rapids are unrunnable.
It's treacherous.

462
00:31:20,567 --> 00:31:22,831
I bet you ran it though,
didn't you?

463
00:31:22,903 --> 00:31:26,566
[Laughing]
I did. I did.

464
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:30,440
I was 18 and completely insane.

465
00:31:30,510 --> 00:31:34,640
- [Laughing]
- I bet you'd like to do it again, right?

466
00:31:34,715 --> 00:31:38,674
- [Maggie Barking]
- Hmm, no.

467
00:31:38,752 --> 00:31:41,448
No, everything's different now.
I have kids and...

468
00:31:41,521 --> 00:31:46,458
- And a husband.
- Yeah, and a husband.

469
00:31:46,526 --> 00:31:49,017
And what if you didn't?

470
00:31:51,832 --> 00:31:53,766
But I do.

471
00:31:56,703 --> 00:32:00,537
[Roarke]
Go get it, Maggie.

472
00:32:00,607 --> 00:32:03,269
Hey, Ro! I got another one
for your collection.

473
00:32:03,343 --> 00:32:06,195
- Hi, Wade!
- Hey, buddy.

474
00:32:06,328 --> 00:32:10,992
But I got the cigarettes too, so we had
ten cartons of cigarettes and no beer.

475
00:32:11,066 --> 00:32:15,833
- I couldn't believe it.
- [Chuckling]

476
00:32:15,904 --> 00:32:18,805
Maggie.
Maggie, no!

477
00:32:18,874 --> 00:32:22,071
Maggie, no!

478
00:32:22,144 --> 00:32:25,307
Maggie, no.
Go lie down. Good girl.

479
00:32:25,380 --> 00:32:31,182
So, Mom, what's this vision quest
thing you told me about?

480
00:32:32,387 --> 00:32:35,288
Vision quest is, um...

481
00:32:35,357 --> 00:32:38,190
is when a boy or a girl
your age...

482
